Why do uploaders take so much time and effort to get good quality in small sizes and then say "Use VLC Media Player to view"? Seems like such a waste, if you're going to suggest a playback method don't suggest something that plays back at lower quality.

Frankly, I don't see the point of releases like this. The source has been compressed so much, it's no better than a DVD Rip.

At this point, image quality would actually go *up* if the video stream was downscaled to fit the bitrate.
